text: 14. MANUSHI print edition has 2b suspended coz 4 yrs all our money, time & energy was consumed dealing with repeated attacks& endless assaults by political goondas cum police with courts not able to offer meaningful relief, except orders which no one in police takes seriously.

name: Madhu Purnima Kishwar
text: 13. BUT IMPLEMENTATION VERY SHODDY & DISHONEST. Exposure to criminal mafias that control police thanas and institutions of governance has been very traumatic.

name: Madhu Purnima Kishwar
text: 12. MAJOR OFFSHOOT of RICKSHAW PIL: Chandni Chowk Redevelopment Project took off in the process of creating dedicated road space for NMVs, full-scale pedestrianization. Only NMVs to ply & motor vehicles prohibited during daytime in redeveloped Chandni Chowk.But... https://t.co/DEsknDm5J0

name: Madhu Purnima Kishwar
text: 11. As part of Rakesh Mehta headed Task Force, I also drafted new law for cycle rickshaws & other NMVs for Delhi Govt in 2011. Old rickshaw law junked thanks to HC and SC judgements in our PILs. But new the high court order was not honestly implemented.

name: Madhu Purnima Kishwar
text: 10. BIG SUCCESS: I was invited to draft a new law for street vendors by the ministry of Urban Affairs. That draft became the basis for new law enacted for the protection of street vendors in 2014.

name: Madhu Purnima Kishwar
text: 9. OPERATION SABOTAGE: Successful experiment invited violent backlash; sabotaged by police & politicians.Led to endless physical attacks by local mafias with police backing. Three violent attacks in the year 2007 could well have been fatal for me.Those court cases still going on https://t.co/yhP1qvdjll

name: Madhu Purnima Kishwar
text:
8. FOURTH BREAKTHROUGH: IAS Rakesh Mehta, then Municipal Commissioner lent us support. IAS Renuka Vishwanathan also joined Manushi Board and became our vigorous advocate.
Mehta allowed us to create two model markets for vendors.

name: Madhu Purnima Kishwar
text: 7. THIRD BREAKTHROUGH: We approached Delhi Court & later Supreme Court in separate PILs. We won multiple battles in both courts. Rickshaw policy declared unconstitutional in 2006. Court banned confiscation of rickshaws. But the ground situation did not improve.

name: Madhu Purnima Kishwar
text:
6. SECOND BREAKTHROUGH: In 2001, then PM A B Vajpayee announced a historic new policy for vendors & rickshaw pullers drafted by then Addl. Sec to PM, Pradipto Ghosh accepting the entire analysis and demand list of Manushi.
But on the ground situation got worse.

name: Madhu Purnima Kishwar
text: 5. FIRST BREAKTHROUGH:  Central Vigilance Commissioner, N.Vittal who presided over two public hearings, was moved by our presentation and sent off letters to CM, PM et al, demanding reform.

name: Madhu Purnima Kishwar
text: 4. At the time, most bureaucrats & police officers, political leaders & even judges were extremely hostile to the presence of these groups in our cities & treated them as an unwanted nuisance. Some even openly called them “vermin, who deserved to be exterminated”.

name: Madhu Purnima Kishwar
text: 3.This included organizing Jan Sunwais (Public Hearings), nagging ministers & officials connected with the noxious laws and policies governing these two sectors plus PILs in Delhi High Court & Supreme Court.

name: Madhu Purnima Kishwar
text: 2.Consequently, I spent the last 23 years working on a lot more ground-level research to assist in advocacy campaign for policy & law reform for street hawkers, rickshaws owners &pullers to encourage the use of eco friendly Non-Motorized Vehicles.

name: Madhu Purnima Kishwar
text: Loktak Lake also houses unique floating wildlife National Park covering 40 sq km out of which approx 15 sq km covered by thick phundis. It is natural habitat of the most endangered species, the brow antlered deer which is hunted for meat by locals.Sadly it was shut the day I went

name: Madhu Purnima Kishwar
text:
The lake vegetation is also harvested as food,fibre,fodder&fuel.Nearly 4000 families depend on this lake for their livlihood. Its water also used for hydropower. Phundis appear in various sizes &shapes. 
View of lake from Assam Rifles Loktak base atop a hillp https://t.co/SzdTGonWN9

name: Madhu Purnima Kishwar
text: Phundis are heterogenous mass of soil,vegetation &organic matter at various stages of decomposition. Phundis appear in different sizes often as ring shaped structures which are used for trapping fish by spreading nets inside. Fishermen float around silently in these tiny canoes https://t.co/6Udz0Wd1DZ
